      <h5>What can they eat?</h5>
      <li>
        Rats can eat just about anything we can eat. Of course, not all of it is good for them! 
        Rats tend to need a diet of fruits/vegetables, and a protein source. They generally require 
        <a href ="http://ratclub.org/ratcare_diet.htm"> 75%-80% of their diet to be carbohydrates</a>. 
        As a treat, rats really enjoy dried rolled oats, small bits of chicken, and even some dog
        treats (as long as they're not low quality)! <br /> 
      </li>
      <li>
        There are a few exceptions to what they can eat. Blue cheese is a hazardous food for them
        because of the mold used to make it. Dried corn contains fungal contaminants, which will
        make a rat very sick.
      </li>
    </ul>
